From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Subject: [PATCH] Expand BOOTKERNEL section to 24 MiB

The default BOOTKERNEL section is 18.75 MiB (0x12C0000), which is no
longer sufficient once the Linux kernel is updated past the 5.10 LTS
line: a 6.12 kernel + initramfs combines to ~24 MiB, overflowing the
slot and causing PnorUtils::checkSpaceConstraints to abort PNOR
assembly.

Grow BOOTKERNEL to 24 MiB (0x1800000) by consuming 5.25 MiB
(0x540000) of previously unallocated space at the tail of the 64 MiB
PNOR. All sections that physically follow BOOTKERNEL (OCC through
HBRT_PROXY) are shifted forward by 0x540000. The new PNOR layout
still fits within the 64 MiB chip with ~60 KiB margin and no
section overlaps.

--- a/p9Layouts/defaultPnorLayout_64.xml
+++ b/p9Layouts/defaultPnorLayout_64.xml
@@ -226,7 +226,7 @@
         <description>Bootloader Kernel (16.67MiB)</description>
         <eyeCatch>BOOTKERNEL</eyeCatch>
         <physicalOffset>0x21C1000</physicalOffset>
-        <physicalRegionSize>0x12C0000</physicalRegionSize>
+        <physicalRegionSize>0x1800000</physicalRegionSize>
         <side>A</side>
         <sha512Version/>
         <readOnly/>
@@ -234,7 +234,7 @@
     <section>
         <description>OCC Lid (1.125MiB)</description>
         <eyeCatch>OCC</eyeCatch>
-        <physicalOffset>0x3481000</physicalOffset>
+        <physicalOffset>0x39C1000</physicalOffset>
         <physicalRegionSize>0x120000</physicalRegionSize>
         <side>A</side>
         <sha512Version/>
@@ -244,7 +244,7 @@
